During the day in the press room only the picture of the president meeting was transferred without sound with the message "private meeting, limited audio".
The few information that circulated among the journalists was received by the press speakers of some of the governments present at the meeting of Unasur, but not by the Peruan press speaker.
The only document that was distributed during the day was the list of participating presidents, which led to the hundreds of journalists of various national and international media discomfort that demanded more information.
After that, the Presidential Office of Peru sent an e-mail to the media with the "closing Statement" of the Summit, but it was the Declaration of Humala and not the official document for the conclusion of the summit.
