The summit also ended with the joint commitment of Chile and Peru to adopt a judgment by the Court of Justice of the Hague, which lays down a cross-border conflict between the two countries.
The Presidents of Peru, Ollanta Humala, and Chile, Sebastián Piñera, met during the regional meeting and confirmed that they would adopt the decision of the IGH, which starts on Monday in Den Haag, in the process that initiated Lima against Santiago to listen to the ployers on both sides.
