The confirmation of both Presidents that they would be subjected to the IGH took place after a decision by Colombia on the maritime borders with Nicaragua, which felt it was a serious mistake, and had raised a complaint against the Bogotá Agreement, which agreed to submit to the judgments of this International Court.
